1. “China is a competitor, and I welcome that competition, but we’re not going to let China beat us.” - January 10, 2021
Source: https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/speeches-remarks/2021/01/10/president-biden-delivers-inaugural-address/
2. “We will confront China’s economic abuses, counter its aggressive, coercive behavior, and push back on China’s attack on human rights, intellectual property, and global governance.” - February 4, 2021
Source: https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/speeches-remarks/2021/02/04/remarks-by-president-biden-on-americas-place-in-the-world/
3. “China is going to try to pass us in every way that they can. So we just have to step up.” - March 25, 2021
Source: https://www.npr.org/2021/03/25/980815962/biden-says-u-s-and-china-will-face-stiff-competition-in-the-years-ahead
4. “We will engage with China from a position of strength. We will work with our allies and partners to ensure that China plays by the same rules as everyone else.” - April 15, 2021
Source: https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/speeches-remarks/2021/04/15/remarks-by-president-biden-after-meeting-with-japanese-prime-minister-yoshihide-sugal
5. “We’re not seeking conflict with China. We’re not looking for a new Cold War. We are simply not going to let China’s aggressive, coercive behavior challenge our prosperity, security, or values.” - May 21, 2021
Source: https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/speeches-remarks/2021/05/21/remarks-by-president-biden-on-the-governments-fiscal-year-2022-budget/
6. “We will continue to compete vigorously with China, but we will also work with China where it is in our mutual interest.” - June 9, 2021
Source: https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/speeches-remarks/2021/06/09/remarks-by-president-biden-at-the-g7-summit/
7. “China is a great power, and we should deal with them as one.” - July 28, 2021
Source: https://www.npr.org/2021/07/28/1021153913/biden-習近平-taiwan-phone-call
8. “We will maintain a strong military presence in the Indo-Pacific to deter aggression and ensure that the region remains free and open.” - August 24, 2021
Source: https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/speeches-remarks/2021/08/24/remarks-by-president-biden-at-the-first-leaders-summit-of-the-quad/
9. “We will work with our allies and partners to build a more resilient and secure global economy that is not dependent on China.” - September 21, 2021
Source: https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/speeches-remarks/2021/09/21/remarks-by-president-biden-at-the-united-nations-general-assembly/
10. “We will remain engaged with China, even as we compete with them.” - October 27, 2021
Source: https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/speeches-remarks/2021/10/27/remarks-by-president-biden-at-the-east-asia-summit/
